						<summary>

						<p>On a slab setup in this village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1603. Durmati, Māgha śu 5, Wednesday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1682 A.D., January 4. Wednesday 10.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. It records the gift of some lands in the village Vēmula by Veṅkaṭādri Timmarasa of Amālimōpalli, while one Maharāyarāja Śrī-Mauroji Aṁto Tirvudhāru mahātātavoyatu was ruling Pulivendla (?).</p>						

						</summary>
